SIMPLE: embosom
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embosom
<hw>Em*bos"om</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>imbosom</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To take into, or place in,
the bosom; to cherish; to foster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Glad to <qex>embosom</qex> his affection.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To inclose or surround; to shelter closely; to place
in the midst of something.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His house <qex>embosomed</qex> in the grove.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Some tender flower . . . .⟦br⟧
<qex>Embosomed</qex> in the greenest glade.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emboss</ent>⟦br⟧
